<br>
There have been many outstanding qualities attributed to the South and to Southerners in this thread. Having lived in the South, I share an affection for the region. I'd like to think that as human beings, we can find another way to express pride in those positive qualities, without displaying a symbol that's so patently offensive to many other Americans.<br>
<br>
I couldn't fully be proud of my heritage if I had to display a symbol that causes someone else real pain. But that's just me, and I do believe you get to do what you want to do, on a personal level. Anyone can display it, just like I get to dislike it. <p><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Gallatin</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
